special_powers.name: MINION: CHAIN OF COMMAND
special_powers.description: When a friendly character with the H.A.M.M.E.R. keyword and a higher point value is within 8 squares, H.A.M.M.E.R. Agent modifies his attack value by +1.  If that character is named Norman Osborn or Iron Patriot, H.A.M.M.E.R. Agent modifies his attack value by an aditional +1.

special_powers.name: MINION: STRONGEST HOST DOMINATES
special_powers.description: When a friendly character named Carnage or Venom is within 8 squares, Symbiote can use Flurry.

special_powers.name: MINION: NOT AN IDEA MAN
special_powers.description: When a friendly character with the Scientist keyword and a higher point value is within 8 squares, Researcher can use Enhancement, but only to affect characters with the Scientist keyword.

special_powers.name: MINION: SERVE AND PROTECT
special_powers.description: When a friendly character with the Police keyword and a higher point value is within 8 squares, Code: Blue Officer can use Willpower.

special_powers.name: SPIDEY SENSE
special_powers.description: Spider-Man can use Super Senses, but evades the attack on a result of 4-6.

special_powers.name: WEB: WEB-SHOOTERS
special_powers.description: Once at the beginning of your turn, if Spider-Man has no action tokens, as a free action he may place a Web special terrain marker in a square occupied by a target opposing character within 6 squares and line of fire.

special_powers.name: ALTER EGO: SPIDER-MAN
special_powers.description: Give this character a power action and replace this character with a #007 Spider-Man or a #022 Spider-Man on its orange starting line. Existing action tokens from this character, as well as action tokens and pushing damage for this action are applied to the replacement. If replaced, no victory points are awarded for this character and the replacement is considered to be its orange point value for all game effects.

special_powers.name: TRAIT
special_powers.description: Venom can use Plasticity.

special_powers.name: WEB: WEB TENDRILS
special_powers.description: Venom can use Telekinesis option 1. If he hits, after Telekinesis is resolved he can place a Web special terrain marker in the destination square.

special_powers.name: ALTER EGO: VENOM
special_powers.description: Give this character a power action and replace this character with a 009 Venom on its orange starting line. Existing action tokens from this character, as well as action tokens and pushing damage for this action are applied to the replacement. If replaced, no victory points are awarded for this character and the replacement is considered to be its orange point value for all game effects.

special_powers.name: ALTER EGO: ANTI-VENOM
special_powers.description: Give this character a power action and replace this character with a 025 Anti-Venom on its orange starting line. Existing action tokens from this character, as well as action tokens and pushing damage for this action are applied to the replacement. If replaced, no victory points are awarded for this character and the replacement is considered to be its orange point value for all game effects.

special_powers.name: REPULSORS UPGRADED
special_powers.description: Once during your turn, Iron Man can use Force Blast as a free action.

special_powers.name: MINION: UPPER CHAIN OF COMMAND
special_powers.description: When a friendly character with the H.A.M.M.E.R. keyword named Norman Osborn or Iron Patriot is within 8 squares, H.A.M.M.E.R. Elite Operative can use Stealth and modifies his attack value by +2.

special_powers.name: SYMBIOTE BLADE
special_powers.description: Whenever Carnage makes a close or ranged combat attack, you may roll a d6. If you do, Carnage's damage value becomes the result and is locked until the attack resolves.

special_powers.name: MASSACRES ARE MY SPECIALTY
special_powers.description: Carnage can use Flurry, Plasticity, and Steal Energy.

special_powers.name: SECRET-IDENTITY HUNTER
special_powers.description: Characters within line of fire can't use Alter Ego powers.

special_powers.name: THE MASTER OF DISGUISE
special_powers.description: Chameleon can use Shape Change, but is successful on a result of 4-6.

special_powers.name: ABSORB AND RE-CHANNEL RADIATION
special_powers.description: Whenever Firestar would take damage from Energy Explosion or Pulse Wave, ignore the damage dealt, heal her of 1 damage, and modify her damage value by +1 until end of turn. This power can't be ignored.

special_powers.name: GETTING THE JOB DONE RIGHT
special_powers.description: Adjacent friendly characters with the Police keyword modify their attack values by +1.

special_powers.name: LIMITED POWER DRAINER
special_powers.description: Lt. Marcus Stone can use Outwit. When he uses Outwit, he can only target a character within 4 squares.

special_powers.name: BACK IN BLACK
special_powers.description: Spider-Man can use Leap/Climb and Stealth.

special_powers.name: WEB: WEB COCOON
special_powers.description: Spider-Man can use Incapacitate as if he had a range of 6. If he hits, you may place a Web special marker in the target character's square.

special_powers.name: UNBALANCED
special_powers.description: Once at the beginning of the game roll a d6. On a roll of 3-4, put a sanity token on this card. On a roll of 5-6, you may choose to put a sanity token on this card.

special_powers.name: ALTER EGO: PATRIOT OF GOBLIN?
special_powers.description: Give this character a power action. If this card has a sanity token, replace this character with a {ws}#039 Iron Patriot. If this card does not have a sanity token, replace this character with a {ws}#058 Green Goblin instead. Begin the replacement on its orange starting line. Existing action tokens from this character, as well as action token and pushing damage for this action are applied to the replacement. If replaced, no victory points are awarded for this character and the replacement is considered to be its orange point value for all game effects.

special_powers.name: ALTER EGO: SCARLET SPIDER
special_powers.description: Give this character a power action and replace this character with a #040 Scarlet Spider on its orange starting line. Existing action tokens from this character, as well as action tokens and pushing damage for this action are applied to the replacement. If replaced, no victory points are awarded for this character and the replacement is considered to be its orange point value for all game effects.

special_powers.name: TEMPORARY FORCED CURE
special_powers.description: Give Anti-Venom a close combat action. If the target takes damage from this close combat attack, all of its powers are countered until end of turn.

special_powers.name: BAD LUCK POWERS
special_powers.description: Black Cat can use Probability Control, but she can only use it during an opponent's turn.  She can use it on each opponent's turn.

special_powers.name: TRIGGER SCENT
special_powers.description: At the beginning of the game, choose an opposing character. X-23 modifies her attack value by +2 when attacking that character.

special_powers.name: KNIFE THROW
special_powers.description: Warpath can use Penetrating/Psychic Blast as if he had a range of 6.

special_powers.name: FORM OF THE WOLF
special_powers.description: Wolfsbane can use Combat Reflexes and Super Senses.

special_powers.name: THE GREATEST ALLY OF ALL
special_powers.description: When a friendly character named Peter Parker or Spider-Man is within 8 squares, Mary Jane Watson can use the Spider-Man team ability.

special_powers.name: MURAMASA DECAPITATION
special_powers.description: Daken can use Blades/Claws/Fangs. If he does, that d6 roll can't be rerolled, and if that roll is 6, the damage dealt is unavoidable damage.

special_powers.name: KINETIC CONTROL
special_powers.description: Vector can use Telekinesis. Opposing characters within 3 squares may be moved with Telekinesis as if they were friendly characters. Opposing characters that are moved in this way may be dealt 1 damage after the action resolves.

special_powers.name: SPIDER-MAN'S A MENACE!
special_powers.description: Characters within line of fire can't use the Spider-Man team ability.

special_powers.name: RAT ARMY (NON-OPTIONAL)
special_powers.description: Vermin uses Battle Fury. At the beginning of your turn, you may deal 1 damage to each opposing character that occupies hindering terrain and is within 2 squares of Vermin.

special_powers.name: TAIL WHIP
special_powers.description: Scorpion can use Quake, but targets all opposing characters within 2 squares unless his line of fire to them is blocked by a wall, blocking or elevated terrain.

special_powers.name: TRAITOR TO ALL
special_powers.description: As you reveal your force, you may choose that Noh-Varr loses all keywords this game. If you do, modify his attack value by +1 this game.

special_powers.name: TRANSFORMING GAUNTLET GUN
special_powers.description: Noh-Varr can use Energy Explosion, Penetrating/Psychic Blast, and Pulse Wave.

special_powers.name: POUNCE FROM ABOVE
special_powers.description: Scarlet Spider can use Leap/Climb.  After he resolves a move action, he can make a close combat attack as a free action.

special_powers.name: WEB: IMPACT WEBBING
special_powers.description: Scarlet Spider can use Energy Explosion as if he had a range of 6.  For each character hit, you may place a Web special marker in that character's square.

special_powers.name: HANG GLIDER
special_powers.description: Cardiac has the [wing] speed symbol.

special_powers.name: PULSE STAFF
special_powers.description: Cardiac can use Energy Explosion. Each character that takes damage from this attack is knocked back 2 squares in addition to the damage taken.

special_powers.name: I NEVER MISS
special_powers.description: Characters targeted by Bullseye can't use Shape Change or Super Senses.

special_powers.name: ANY OBJECT A WEAPON
special_powers.description: Bullseye can use Super Strength, but he cannot pick up or carry heavy objects. If he hits with an attack using an object, after the attack is resolved, deal 1 penetrating damage to his target.

special_powers.name: CONTINUAL HEALING FACTOR
special_powers.description: Once at the beginning of your turn, as a free action you may heal Wolverine of 1 damage.

special_powers.name: RELUCTANT BUT BRUTAL LEADER
special_powers.description: Wolverine can use Leadership. If Wolverine succeeds in his Leadership roll, you may also remove an action token from an adjacent friendly character with the X-Force keyword, then deal that character 1 unavoidable damage.

special_powers.name: AIN'T NOTHING GOIN' TO STOP ME
special_powers.description: Rocket Racer ignores all terrain for movement purposes except indoor walls and indoor blocking terrain.

special_powers.name: WHILE SOLO LIVES, TERROR DIES!
special_powers.description: If Solo has no action tokens, you may give him a power action to use Phasing/Teleport, and after the action resolves, he can then make a ranged combat attack as a free action.

special_powers.name: CLONE MADNESS
special_powers.description: Characters on your force modify their attack values by +2 and their damage values by +1 when attacking an opposing character under 300 points with their exact same name.

special_powers.name: CLONE MASTER
special_powers.description: If two or more friendly characters adjacent to Jackal have the exact same name as one another, those characters can all use Shape Change if they can't already.

special_powers.name: EXTRA-DIMENSIONAL TELEPORTATION
special_powers.description: Nightcrawler ignores the effects of terrain and characters on movement.

special_powers.name: TELEPORTATION EVACUATION
special_powers.description: Nightcrawler can use Hypersonic Speed, Stealth and the Carry Ability. When Nightcrawler uses Hypersonic Speed, a target hit by a close combat attack may be placed adjacent to Nightcrawler after the power action resolves.

special_powers.name: BAMF!
special_powers.description: Nightcrawler can use Super Senses. Whenever he uses Super Senses to evade an attack, you may immediately move him up to half of his speed value.

special_powers.name: INTANGIBLE ENERGY FORM
special_powers.description: Ignore all but 1 damage dealt to X-Ray by close combat attacks.

special_powers.name: PLANT GROWTH
special_powers.description: Once during your turn, as a free action you may heal Groot 1 damage if he occupies hindering or water terrain.

special_powers.name: FLORAL COLOSSUS SPROUT
special_powers.description: Non-optional. Groot has the Colossal damage symbol, a range of 4, and can't be moved.

special_powers.name: MAJOR EARTHQUAKE
special_powers.description: Give Red Hulk a power action and make a close combat attack targeting each character within 3 squares. Each character hit is dealt damage equal to 4 minus the number of squares it is from red hulk. Characters who can use flight ability automatically evade this attack.

special_powers.name: OUT OF THE...SPOTS?
special_powers.description: Once per turn, before The Spot is given a close combat action, you may place him in any square within 6 squares and line of fire that's also adjacent to a wall, blocking terrain or is a grounded square adjacent to elevated terrain.

special_powers.name: TRANS-DIMENSIONAL SPOTS
special_powers.description: The Spot can use Flurry and Phasing/Teleport.

special_powers.name: PSYCHIC VAMPIRE
special_powers.description: Morlun can use Steal Energy. Whenever Morlun is healed using Steal Energy, you may place a tracking token on the targeted character's card.

special_powers.name: RELENTLESS PURSUIT
special_powers.description: Give Morlun a power action. You may place him in a square adjacent to an opposing character within his line of fire who has a tracking token, then target that character with a close combat attack as a free action.

special_powers.name: SINISTER MASTERMIND
special_powers.description: Adjacent friendly characters possessing the Sinister Syndicate team ability can't have their Speed or Attack powers countered.

special_powers.name: FOUR ARMS AND FOUR EYES
special_powers.description: Doctor Octopus can use Perplex four times during your turn, but only to modify his own combat values.

special_powers.name: TENTACLE FLURRY
special_powers.description: Doctor Octopus can use Flurry.

special_powers.name: SAND SMOTHER
special_powers.description: Sandman can use Stealth and Plasticity. Whenever an adjacent opposing character fails to break away, deal that character 1 unavoidable damage after the action resolves.

special_powers.name: MIND-NUMBING GAS
special_powers.description: Opposing characters that occupy a square with a hindering terrain marker placed by Mysterio at the beginning or end of an action can't use Indomitable, Super Senses, or Willpower until the end of that turn.

special_powers.name: THE GRAND REVEAL
special_powers.description: Give Mysterio a power action and choose a friendly character with a single base. Mysterio and the chosen character are placed in each others squares. Neither character can be given another action this turn.

special_powers.name: RIDICULOUS REGENERATION
special_powers.description: Whenever Deadpool would be dealt damage from an attack, roll a d6 instead. On a result of 1, he takes that damage plus 1. On a result of a 2-3 he takes the normal amount of damage. On a result of a 4-5 he takes 1 damage. On a result of a 6, he heals 1 damage instead.

special_powers.name: PUMPKIN BOMB BARRAGE
special_powers.description: Green Goblin can use Energy Explosion. He can use it normally, or he can use it as if he had 3 targets and a range of 4.

special_powers.name: GOBLIN GLIDER
special_powers.description: Green Goblin can use Combat Reflexes and Toughness.

special_powers.name: ALL-OUT ASSAULT
special_powers.description: Once per game, give Iron Man/War Machine a power action that places two action tokens on them. Iron Man/War Machine possess [1 target] for this action. They can make up to 4 close and/or ranged combat attacks as free actions. An opposing character may only be targeted once during this action. After resolving this action, Iron Man/War Machine are dealt 1 unavoidable damage.

special_powers.name: ADAPTIVE RESPONSE ARMOR
special_powers.description: When Iron Man/War Machine uses the Duo Attack ability, they may choose Incapacitate, Penetrating/Psychic Blast, or Ranged Combat Expert and use that instead of one or both ranged combat attacks.

special_powers.name: GASEOUS STATE
special_powers.description: Vapor can use Smoke Cloud.  If she does, modify her defense value by +2 until the beginning of your next turn.  Whenever a hindering terrain marker placed by her is removed from the map, you may place her in that square.

special_powers.name: SPIDER-SMASH
special_powers.description: Spider-Hulk can use Leap/Climb. If he ends a move action adjacent to three or more opposing characters, he can use Quake as a free action.

special_powers.name: ROOF RIP
special_powers.description: Give Spider-Hulk a power action if he occupies elevated terrain. All elevated terrain within the same continuous border as Spider-Hulk becomes grounded hindering terrain, and deal each other character occupying an affected square 2 damage.

special_powers.name: REPLACE THE SPIDER
special_powers.description: Doppelganger can use Exploit Weakness, but only to target characters named "Spider-Man" or characters possessing the Spider-Man team ability. When he does, the target cannot use team abilities and the attack cannot be evaded.

special_powers.name: TWISTED CLONE
special_powers.description: Doppelganger can use Combat Reflexes and Leap/Climb.

special_powers.name: MINION: MINDLESS PAWN
special_powers.description: Once per turn, if Doppelganger has exactly one action token, you may give a power action to a friendly character with a higher point value within 8 squares. You may now give Doppelganger one action as a free action.

special_powers.name: KICK ME!
special_powers.description: Whenever Bombastic Bag-Man takes damage from an attack, deal the attacker penetrating damage equal to the damage taken by Bombastic Bag-Man. Bombastic Bag-Man can't be healed except by the Fantastic Four team ability.

special_powers.name: PSYCHIC WEBBING
special_powers.description: Cosmic Spider-Man can use Incapacitate. If he hits, he can use Telekinesis option 1 as a free action targeting one of the characters hit by Incapacitate.

special_powers.name: ENIGMA FORCE BLAST
special_powers.description: Cosmic Spider-Man can use Force Blast. If he does so, he can then use Ranged Combat Expert as a free action targeting the same character.

special_powers.name: UNI-VISION
special_powers.description: Cosmic Spider-Man's line of fire is never blocked.

special_powers.name: WEB SWING THROUGH THE CITY
special_powers.description: Spider-Man can use Leap/Climb. Once per turn, if Spider-Man has no action tokens, he can be given a move action as a free action if he ends his movement adjacent to the rim of elevated terrain.

special_powers.name: WEB: FIRST WEBS
special_powers.description: Spider-Man has a range of 6. If he hits with any attack, you may place a Web special terrain marker in his target's square after the action resolves.

special_powers.name: WEB: INVASIVE ORGANIC WEBBING
special_powers.description: Venom can use Penetrating/Psychic Blast as if he had a range of 6. If he hits, you may place a Web special terrain marker in his target's square after the action resolves.

special_powers.name: PROTECTED CONVALESCENCE
special_powers.description: Night Nurse can use Support.  After that action resolves, modify her target's defense value by +1 until the beginning of your next turn.

special_powers.name: NEW SYMBIOTE
special_powers.description: Toxin can use Plasticity and Shape Change.

special_powers.name: SMELL THROUGH DISGUISE
special_powers.description: Opposing characters within 6 squares can't use Shape Change.

special_powers.name: BACKSTAB
special_powers.description: Modify Daken's damage value by +1 for each action token on the target of his attack.

special_powers.name: AMBUSH THE INNOCENT
special_powers.description: "The Burglar" modifies his attack and damage values by +2 when attacking a character with a lower point cost.

special_powers.name: Prerequisites
special_powers.description: [boot] and a point value of 150 or less
Choose a character. This character can use the Swim ability.
A character occupying this square must break away for movement purposes. Immediately after the character occupying this square no longer occupies it, remove this marker from the map.
A character occupying this square must break away for movement purposes. Immediately after the character occupying this square no longer occupies it, remove this marker from the map.
